title.narrative: ACCESS TO INTEGRATED SOCIAL SERVICES, INCLUDING IN HUMANITARIAN SETTINGS

description.narrative: By 2022, vulnerable families with children and those with children with delays and disabilities have access to social services in selected communities, including in humanitarian settings, which contributes to Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance, Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance (Covid), Children With Disabilities, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, the most vulnerable children in Ukraine benefit from more-child-friendly and family-oriented social welfare and justice systems.
